	<section id="label">

		<h3>Label</h3>
		<p>Use labels to display requirements, or other important information. Include @@mixin <code>label</code> to turn any <code>span</code> element into a label. Additional @@mixins are provided to alter the style to change emphasis. Optional styles to provide a <code>label</code> class, and the various styles, are provided for convenience.</p>

		<div class="example">

			<span class="label">default</span>
			<span class="label primary">primary</span>
			<span class="label positive">positive</span>
			<span class="label warning">warning</span>
			<span class="label negative">negative</span>

		</div>

		<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-markup">&lt;span class="label"&gt;info&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="label primary"&gt;required&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="label positive"&gt;success&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="label warning"&gt;warning&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="label negative"&gt;error&lt;/span&gt;</code></pre>

		<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-css">.label {
	@@include label;
    &.primary {
        @@include label-primary;
    }
    &.positive {
        @@include label-positive;
    }
    &.warning {
        @@include label-warning;
    }
    &.negative {
        @@include label-negative;
    }
}</code></pre>

	</section>

	<section id="modal">

