	<section id="tag">

		<h3>Tag</h3>
		<p>Use tags to display additional information such as item counts or categories. Include @@mixin <code>tag</code> to turn any <code>span</code> element into a tag. Additional @@mixins are provided to alter the style to change emphasis. Optional styles to provide a <code>tag</code> class, and the various styles, are provided for convenience.</p>

			<div class="example">

				<span class="tag">default</span>
				<span class="tag primary">primary</span>
				<span class="tag positive">positive</span>
				<span class="tag warning">warning</span>
				<span class="tag negative">negative</span>

			</div>

			<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-markup">&lt;span class="tag"&gt;default&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="tag primary"&gt;primary&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="tag positive"&gt;positive&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="tag warning"&gt;warning&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="tag negative"&gt;negative&lt;/span&gt;</code></pre>

			<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-css">.tag {
	@@include tag;
    &.primary {
        @@include tag-primary;
    }
    &.positive {
        @@include tag-positive;
    }
    &.warning {
        @@include tag-warning;
    }
    &.negative {
        @@include tag-negative;
    }
}</code></pre>

	</section>

